author: CNN
description:
A complex investigation into the Brown University shooting is underway, Providence Police Chief Col. Oscar L. Perez Jr. said Sunday. Authorities are not yet releasing any names involved in the investigation, the police chief said.

The victims who remain hospitalized are receiving “extraordinary” care and show “courage and hope,” the mayor of Providence said. “These survivors are receiving excellent care and the resilience that these survivors showed and shared with me is, frankly, pretty overwhelming,” Mayor Brett Smiley said, who added he has visited a few victims and their families. The mayor commended the professionalism of the first responders, law enforcement and hospital staff.

CNN correspondent Brian Todd reports from Providence.  #CNN #News
title: Officials provide update on Brown University shooting and investigation

author: CNN
description:
A person of interest is in custody in connection with the shooting at Brown University, officials said early Sunday. The Saturday shooting, which happened during a final exam review session at the private Ivy League university, left two students dead and nine others injured. A CNN crew witnessed heavy police activity overnight at a hotel in the Providence, Rhode Island, area that law enforcement officials at the scene said was “connected” to the shooting. A shelter-in-place order that was in effect for much of the campus after the shooting has been lifted, the university said Sunday morning.

CNN's Dana Bash speaks with Providence mayor Brett Smiley. #CNN #News
title: Officials: Person detained after 2 killed in Brown University shooting

author: CNN
description:
A fatal shooting incident took place at Australia’s popular Bondi Beach on Sunday, in an attack that police said targeted the country’s Jewish community. At least 11 people were killed in the attack, with another 29 injured, police said at a press conference. No details have yet been given about the victims of the shooting.

Of the two suspected attackers, one is in custody in critical condition and the other was shot dead at the scene, according to police. Authorities have so far not provided any details about the identities of these suspects.

More than 1,000 people were attending a Hanukkah celebration at Bondi Beach when the shooting occurred, police said, adding that the attack was “designed to target Sydney’s Jewish community.” The fact the shooting took place on the first day of Hanukkah, as well other circumstances including the types of weapons at the scene and the offenders, led a terrorist incident to be declared a few hours after the attack, police said.

CNN producer Angu
title: At least 11 killed in attack on Australia's Jewish community
